synthmodem
==========

synthmodem is licensed under the GNU General Public License,
version 2 (GPL-2.0-or-later). See licenses/GPL-2.0.txt for the
complete license text.

This COPYING file is the master license document for every
synthmodem release. Any binary or source distribution must
include this file, the licenses/ directory, and the upstream
notices referenced below.

For the maintainer-side workflow that produces distributable
releases (vendoring sources, rebuilding prebuilts, satisfying
GPL §3(a) corresponding-source obligations), see MAINTAINERS.md.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS BUNDLED IN THIS DISTRIBUTION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. slmodemd source (vm/slmodemd/*.c, *.h)
   Copyright (c) Smart Link Ltd. and contributors.
   License: 3-clause BSD as published by Smart Link (see
            vm/slmodemd/COPYING and licenses/SLMODEMD-BSD-3.txt),
            with modifications by the D-Modem / synexo project
            contributed under GPL-2.0-or-later.
   The combined work is effectively GPL-2.0-or-later by virtue of
   the GPL'd modifications.
   Source: https://github.com/synexo/D-Modem (slmodemd/ subtree),
           pinned commit recorded in vm/slmodemd/UPSTREAM.txt.

2. Smart Link DSP blob (vm/slmodemd/dsplibs.o)
   Copyright (c) Smart Link Ltd.
   License: proprietary, redistribution permitted per Smart Link's
            grant to the Debian sl-modem-daemon package. See
            licenses/DSPLIBS-NOTICE for the exact terms and the
            obligations they impose on redistribution.
   This file is a closed-source 32-bit i386 ELF object. No source
   is available. It is used only when the slmodemd-pjsip backend
   is active (config.modem.backend = 'slmodemd-pjsip'); the
   default 'native' backend does not link against it.

3. d-modem glue (vm/d-modem/d-modem.c)
   Copyright (C) 2021 Aon plc.
   License: GPL-2.0-or-later. See licenses/D-MODEM-NOTICE for
            attribution details and licenses/GPL-2.0.txt for the
            full license text.
   Vendored verbatim from https://github.com/synexo/D-Modem, pinned
   commit recorded in vm/d-modem/UPSTREAM.txt. Builds against PJSIP
   (entry 4) and slmodemd (entry 1) to produce vm/prebuilt/d-modem,
   the backend helper used when config.modem.backend = 'slmodemd-pjsip'.

4. PJSIP / pjproject (vm/sources/pjproject-2.15.1.tar.gz)
   Copyright (C) 2003-2024 Teluu Inc. and contributors.
   License: PJSIP is dual-licensed (GPL-2.0-or-later, or a Teluu
            commercial license). synthmodem redistributes under the
            GPL-2.0-or-later option. See licenses/PJSIP-NOTICE for
            attribution, upstream pointers, and dual-license details.
   Upstream release 2.15.1, fetched from
   https://github.com/pjsip/pjproject/archive/refs/tags/2.15.1.tar.gz
   and pinned by SHA256 in scripts/fetch-vm-sources.sh. The tarball
   in vm/sources/ is unpacked inside the bookworm build VM and
   statically linked into vm/prebuilt/d-modem. Our build-time
   customization (empty config_site.h at vendor time) lives at
   vm/pjsip/config_site.h; no PJSIP source files are modified.

5. modemd-tunnel (vm/tunnel/*.c, *.h)
   Copyright (C) 2026 synthmodem contributors.
   License: GPL-2.0-or-later.
   Standalone i386 helper that bridges UDP datagrams between Node
   on the host and PJSIP inside the runtime VM over a TCP virtio-
   serial chardev. Source is in-tree; no upstream pin. Wire
   protocol is documented in vm/tunnel/PROTOCOL.md.

6. modemd-ctrl (vm/ctrl/*.c, *.h)
   Copyright (C) 2026 synthmodem contributors.
   License: GPL-2.0-or-later.
   Standalone i386 helper that bridges slmodemd's PTY to the Node
   host over a TCP virtio-serial chardev. Source is in-tree; no
   upstream pin. Used by the slmodemd-pjsip backend so Node can
   drive AT commands and exchange data-mode bytes with slmodemd.

7. spandsp-derived JavaScript code (src/dsp/V8Sequencer.js,
   src/dsp/protocols/V22Demodulator.js, src/dsp/protocols/V22RxRRC.js,
   src/dsp/protocols/V22Common.js, src/dsp/protocols/V22.js,
   src/dsp/protocols/FskCommon.js)
   Original copyright: Copyright (C) 2003-2009 Steve Underwood
                       <steveu@coppice.org>.
   JavaScript port:    synthmodem contributors, 2026.
   Upstream license:   LGPL-2.1 (https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp).
   License as redistributed by synthmodem: GPL-2.0-or-later, via the
            LGPL-2.1 §3 election to relicense LGPL-2.1 work under
            the ordinary GPL. See licenses/SPANDSP-NOTICE for the
            list of files affected, the per-file ports they derive
            from, the documented adaptations, and the rationale for
            the §3 election. The LGPL-2.1 text (as the upstream
            license) is at licenses/LGPL-2.1.txt; the GPL-2.0 text
            (as the as-redistributed license) is at
            licenses/GPL-2.0.txt.
   No spandsp C/C++ source is shipped; the prior native addons in
   src/native/ were removed in cleanup-phase-2. The spandsp upstream
   tree is not vendored — see SPANDSP-NOTICE for the
   corresponding-source analysis.

8. Linux kernel (vm/sources/linux_*.tar.xz)
   Copyright (C) Linus Torvalds and contributors.
   License: GPL-2.0-only WITH Linux-syscall-note exception (the
            standard kernel licensing per the upstream COPYING file
            — the syscall exception clarifies that user-space
            programs invoking kernel services through normal system
            calls are not derivative works). See
            licenses/LINUX-KERNEL-NOTICE for upstream pointers,
            version pin, and corresponding-source details.
   Debian bookworm linux-image-6.1.0-42-686-pae-unsigned. We
   redistribute the compiled kernel image at vm/kernel/bzImage
   plus selected modules at vm/kernel/modules/. Corresponding
   source under vm/sources/ (split tarball; see
   vm/sources/README.md for reassembly).

9. busybox (vm/sources/busybox_*.tar.bz2)
   Copyright (C) Erik Andersen and contributors.
   License: GPL-2.0-only (busybox 1.3.0 and later are GPLv2-only;
            the "or later" option does not apply). See
            licenses/BUSYBOX-NOTICE for upstream pointers, version
            pin, and corresponding-source details.
   Debian bookworm busybox-static. We redistribute the compiled
   binary at vm/busybox/busybox. Corresponding source under
   vm/sources/.

10. glibc (vm/sources/glibc_*.tar.xz)
    Copyright (C) Free Software Foundation and contributors.
    License: LGPL-2.1-or-later. See licenses/GLIBC-NOTICE for
             upstream pointers, version pin, the §6 relinking
             posture, and corresponding-source details.
    Debian bookworm libc6 (glibc 2.36-9+deb12u13). We redistribute
    selected shared libraries (ld-linux.so.2, libc.so.6, libm.so.6)
    at vm/libc/. Corresponding source under vm/sources/.

11. Node.js (win/nodejs/)
    Copyright (c) Node.js contributors. All rights reserved.
    License: MIT. See licenses/NODEJS-LICENSE for the complete
             license text (which also covers Node.js's bundled
             third-party libraries such as V8, libuv, OpenSSL,
             etc., each under their own permissive terms as
             enumerated in that file).
    This component is included only in the Windows distribution
    at win/nodejs/ and is not part of the Linux distribution.
    Corresponding source: win/nodejs-release/node-v25.9.0-win.x64.zip
    MIT does not require source distribution, but the source is
    included for completeness.

12. QEMU (win/qemu/)
    Copyright (c) QEMU contributors. See the QEMU source tree for
    individual file copyrights.
    License: GPL-2.0. See licenses/QEMU-NOTICE for attribution and
             corresponding-source details, and licenses/GPL-2.0.txt
             for the complete license text.
    Version: 11.0.50. This component is included only in the Windows
    distribution at win/qemu/ and is not part of the Linux distribution.
    Corresponding source: win/qemu-source/qemu-master.zip

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GPL CORRESPONDING-SOURCE STATEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Because this distribution contains GPL-licensed binaries, anyone
receiving a binary distribution is entitled to the complete
corresponding source code for those binaries.

The synthmodem repository IS the corresponding source:

  - All Node.js code under src/, vm/qemu-runner/, test/. This
    includes the spandsp-derived JS modules listed in entry 7;
    those .js files are themselves the distributable source form.
  - All C code for modemd-tunnel and modemd-ctrl, in-tree under
    vm/tunnel/ and vm/ctrl/.
  - The vendored slmodemd source under vm/slmodemd/, including
    UPSTREAM.txt recording the exact commit fetched.
  - The vendored d-modem.c source under vm/d-modem/, including
    UPSTREAM.txt recording the D-Modem commit and the file SHA256.
  - The vendored PJSIP release tarball under vm/sources/
    (pjproject-*.tar.gz), with SHA256 pinned in
    scripts/fetch-vm-sources.sh and release metadata in
    vm/pjsip/UPSTREAM.txt. Our PJSIP build customization
    (vm/pjsip/config_site.h) and d-modem build recipe
    (vm/d-modem/Makefile) are in-tree.
  - The vendored Linux kernel, busybox, and glibc source tarballs
    under vm/sources/ (linux_*, busybox_*, glibc_* — see
    vm/sources/README.md for the full inventory).
  - The QEMU source tarball for the Windows distribution, at
    win/qemu-source/qemu-master.zip, corresponding to the prebuilt
    QEMU binaries at win/qemu/. See licenses/QEMU-NOTICE.
  - The Node.js source for the Windows distribution, at
    win/nodejs-release/node-v25.9.0-win.x64.zip, corresponding to
    the Node.js runtime at win/nodejs/. (MIT-licensed; included for
    completeness only.)
  - The build recipes: vm/Makefile, scripts/fetch-vm-sources.sh,
    scripts/fetch-vm-binaries.sh, scripts/build-slmodemd-in-vm.sh,
    scripts/build-pjsip-in-vm.sh.

The proprietary dsplibs.o is NOT GPL'd and is not subject to the
GPL's corresponding-source requirement. It is redistributed under
its own permissive terms (see licenses/DSPLIBS-NOTICE).

The spandsp upstream C source tree is NOT vendored. synthmodem
does not distribute any compiled spandsp binary, and the
corresponding-source obligation attaches to what is distributed
(the JavaScript ports, which are themselves source). Recipients
who wish to compare the ports against upstream may use the
file/line citations in each ported module to consult spandsp
directly at https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp. See
licenses/SPANDSP-NOTICE.

See MAINTAINERS.md for the operational procedure (vendoring
script invocations, GPL compliance checklist, and the offline
rebuild workflow).

